Dane wykorzystane do przygotowania wizualizacji pochodzą ze stron: “https://www.facebook.com/csplatvija/” i “https://www.csb.gov.lv/lv/statistika/statistikai-100”. Są także przedstawione na poniższym wykresie:

Kod tworzący wizualizację

nad_baltyk <- map_data("world2") %>% 
  filter(region %in% c("Poland", "Sweden", "Latvia", "Lithuania", "Estonia", "Finland", "Denmark", "Germany"))

nad_baltyk <- mutate(nad_baltyk, students_per_10000 = 0)

nad_baltyk$students_per_10000 <- ifelse(nad_baltyk$region == "Poland", 10.7, nad_baltyk$students_per_10000)
nad_baltyk$students_per_10000 <- ifelse(nad_baltyk$region == "Sweden", 19.6, nad_baltyk$students_per_10000)
nad_baltyk$students_per_10000 <- ifelse(nad_baltyk$region == "Estonia", 37.7, nad_baltyk$students_per_10000)
nad_baltyk$students_per_10000 <- ifelse(nad_baltyk$region == "Latvia", 30, nad_baltyk$students_per_10000)
nad_baltyk$students_per_10000 <- ifelse(nad_baltyk$region == "Lithuania", 8.2, nad_baltyk$students_per_10000)
nad_baltyk$students_per_10000 <- ifelse(nad_baltyk$region == "Finland", 9.7, nad_baltyk$students_per_10000)
nad_baltyk$students_per_10000 <- ifelse(nad_baltyk$region == "Germany", 11.4, nad_baltyk$students_per_10000)
nad_baltyk$students_per_10000 <- ifelse(nad_baltyk$region == "Denmark", 11.8, nad_baltyk$students_per_10000)

theme_nothing <- theme(
  axis.text = element_blank(),
  axis.line = element_blank(),
  axis.ticks = element_blank(),
  panel.border = element_blank(),
  panel.grid = element_blank(),
  axis.title = element_blank())

ggplot() +
  geom_polygon(data = nad_baltyk, aes(x=long, y = lat, fill = students_per_10000, group = group), color = "white") + 
  coord_fixed(1.6) +
  scale_fill_gradient2(low = "seashell",
                       mid = "deeppink1",
                       high = "deeppink4",
                       midpoint = 20) +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(title = expression(bold("Liczba studentów na 10 000 mieszkańców")), subtitle = expression(bold("w krajach nadbałtyckich w 1928 roku")), 
       x = "", 
       y = "", 
       fill = "Liczba studentów") +
  expand_limits(x = c(15,25))
